Our FACE the Challenge fundraiser would be a project that we feel would be very beneficial.  It's a 1/2 day virtual event that will take place in September that would include a walk/run as well as 30 minute educational sessions in which there would be 2 running at the same time.

Our budget could be as high as $10,000. 
We are interested in having assistance with:


**We do not need you to recruit participants for the event.  

Below are some examples of the educational sessions that we mentioned above:
1. Physical Therapy role in the treatment of facial palsy
2. Physical Therapy role in the treatment of TMD
3. Ophthalmic intervention for facial palsy
4. Botox and surgical options for the treatment of facial palsy
5. Dental intervention in the treatment of TMD
6. Regenerative medicine role in the treatment of facial palsy
7. Regenerative medicine role in the treatment of TMD
8. Relaxation and Stress Management techniques

If you should want to review more about the FACE the Challenge event please do so here: http://foundationforfacialrecovery.org/face-the-challenge.html

Tens of thousands of men, women and children are diagnosed each year with facial paralysis caused by conditions such as Bell’s Palsy, Synkinesis, Ramsay Hunt, Lyme Disease, Acoustic Neuroma, Congenital Facial Palsy, Parotid Tumor, and many other causes, as well as TMD / TMJ disorders (Temporomandibular disorder).  These conditions get little to no acknowledgement and millions of people are suffering from pain along with emotional distress with these conditions.

We at the Foundation for Facial Recovery want these individuals to know they are not alone and there is hope and help!

Last year our first annual FACE the Challenge event raised over $17,532 that will go towards research projects to improve facial palsy and TMJ disorder.  With your help (see above our needs) we really feel we can reach our goals this year and help those who are suffering from these conditions.
